title: 2017 Macbook pro  A1701 820-00928-a not booting
message:
Hi.
I have a problem with 820-00928-a   . This mac is not booting . Some times it says that something is wrong and needs to reboot and keep rebooting. Some times the apple logo appear  and remain stuck at spinning circle. If i enter in apple diag.  and do a ssd diag. it keep searching  the ssd but it see nothing. The motherboard is clean  and no corrosion present.   The beauties is that the ssd is soldered on motherboard. Can you give some idea  where to start?
Thx.

title: 2017 Macbook pro  A1701 820-00928-a not booting
message:
Start with USB-C OSX and try to access internal SSD.
Be sure J9600 makes good contacts.

title: 2017 Macbook pro  A1701 820-00928-a not booting
message: Try new BIOS with clean ME, just in case.

title: 2017 Macbook pro  A1701 820-00928-a not booting
message:
Try to boot preinstalled USB OSX, with J9500 removed.
Also try to start in safe mode.
If your machine is touchbar model, check corresponding thread about critical update error on this case.
